  "grammar_point": {
    "title": "Adjectives with 真 (zhēn) and 很 (hěn)",
    "explanation": "In Chinese, adjectives often need an intensifier. 真 (zhēn) means 'really' and 很 (hěn) means 'very'. Unlike English, no linking verb is needed: 她很高 literally means 'she very tall'. The particle 的 (de) shows possession: 你的 = your.",
    "examples": [
